headline: 62-year-old fast-food Mexican chain quietly closing restaurants
summary: “In the fast‑food Mexican business, there’s Taco Bell — and there’s everyone else,” wrote Restaurant Business Online's Jonathan Maze. He’s not discounting Chipotle, which competes in the fast‑casual segment, but combined with Taco Bell, these behemoths show why chains like Del Taco have struggled ...
